<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <head>
      <style>
        body {
          font-family: sans-serif;
          text-align: center;
          background-color: #f3f3f3;
          color: #333;
        }
        ul {
          list-style: none;
        }
        li {
          display: inline-block;
          margin: 0 10px;
        }
        a {
          text-decoration: none;
          color: #333;
        }
        a:hover {
          color: #0074d9;
        }
        h1 {
          font-size: 32px;
          margin: 20px 0;
          color: #333;
        }
        p {
          font-size: 18px;
          margin: 20px 0;
          color: #666;
        }
        .section {
          max-width: 800px;
          margin: 20px auto;
          padding: 20px;
          background-color: #fff;
          box-shadow: 0 2px 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        .section h2 {
          font-size: 24px;
          margin: 10px 0;
          color: #333;
        }
        .section p {
          font-size: 16px;
          margin: 10px 0;
          color: #666;
        }
        input[type="text"],
        input[type="password"] {
          width: 100%;
          padding: 12px 20px;
          margin: 8px 0;
          box-sizing: border-box;
          border: 2px solid #ccc;
          border-radius: 4px;
        }

        input[type="submit"] {
          width: 100%;
          background-color: #4caf50;
          color: white;
          padding: 14px 20px;
          margin: 8px 0;
          border: none;
          border-radius: 4px;
          cursor: pointer;
        }

        input[type="submit"]:hover {
          background-color: #45a049;
        }
        ::-webkit-scrollbar {
          width: 12px;
          height: 12px;
        }

        ::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb {
          background-color: #666;
          border-radius: 10px;
          transition: background-color 0.2s ease;
        }

        ::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb:hover {
          background-color: #333;
        }

        ::-webkit-scrollbar-track {
          background-color: #333;
          transition: background-color 0.2s ease;
        }

        ::-webkit-scrollbar-track:hover {
          background-color: #666;
        }

        .banner {
          width: 100%;
          height: 60px;
          background-color: #45a049;
          text-align: center;
          font-size: 18px;
          font-weight: bold;
          padding: 10px 0;
          color: #666;
        }

        .close-button {
          position: absolute;
          top: 10px;
          right: 10px;
          font-size: 18px;
          font-weight: bold;
          border: none;
          background: transparent;
          cursor: pointer;
        }

        footer {
          background-color: #333;
          color: #fff;
          text-align: center;
          padding: 20px;
        }

        footer p {
          margin: 0;
          font-size: 14px;
        }

        /* Dark mode styles */
        @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
          body {
            background-color: #333;
            color: #fff;
          }
          .section {
            background-color: #444;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 2px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
          }
          .section h1,
          .section h2,
          .section p,
          a {
            color: #ccc;
          }
          h1,
          h2,
          p,
          a {
            color: #ccc;
          }
        }
      </style>
    </head>
    <body>
      <div class="banner">
        <p>
          Announcement: Currently, we are not taking in-person classes due to a
          shortage of tutors.
        </p>
        <button class="close-button" onclick="hideBanner()">Close</button>
        <script>
          function hideBanner() {
            document.querySelector(".banner").style.display = "none";
          }
        </script>
      </div>
      <h1>Welcome to Ruby Education</h1>
      <p>
        This page is designed to help you learn more about a topic of your
        choice.
      </p>
      <div class="section">
        <h2>Sign Up/Log In</h2>
        <form action="/auth" method="POST">
          <label for="username">Username:</label><br />
          <input type="text" id="username" name="username" /><br />
          <label for="password">Password:</label><br />
          <input type="password" id="password" name="password" /><br /><br />
          <%= Rack::Csrf.tag(env) %>
          <input type="submit" />
        </form>
      </div>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/math">Math</a></li>
        <li><a href="/science">Science</a></li>
        <li><a href="/history">History</a></li>
        <li><a href="/language">Language</a></li>
        <li><a href="/art">Art</a></li>
        <li><a href="/music">Music</a></li>
        <li><a href="/technology">Technology</a></li>
        <li><a href="/physical-education">Physical Education</a></li>
      </ul>
      <div class="section">
        <h2>Math</h2>
        <p>
          Math is the study of numbers, quantities, and shapes. It is a
          fundamental subject that is essential for understanding many other
          subjects and for solving problems in everyday life.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="section">
        <h2>Science</h2>
        <p>
          Science is the systematic study of the physical and natural world
          through observation and experimentation. It is a broad field that
          encompasses many different disciplines, including biology, chemistry,
          physics, and earth science.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="section">
        <h2>History</h2>
        <p>
          History is the study of past events and the way they have shaped the
          world we live in today. It encompasses a wide range of subjects,
          including political, social, cultural, and economic history.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="section">
        <h2>Language</h2>
        <p>
          Language is the system of communication that is used by humans. It can
          be spoken, written, or signed, and it is made up of words and grammar.
          There are thousands of different languages in the world, each with its
          own unique characteristics and history.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="section">
        <h2>Art</h2>
        <p>
          Art is the expression of human creativity and imagination through
          various mediums, such as painting, sculpture, drawing, and
          photography. It encompasses a wide range of styles and movements, from
          traditional to modern and abstract. Art can be used to convey
          emotions, tell stories, and communicate ideas.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="section">
        <h2>Music</h2>
        <p>
          Music is a universal form of artistic expression that involves the
          organization of sound and silence. It is created using a variety of
          instruments, such as guitars, pianos, and drums, and it can be
          performed by solo artists or by groups, such as orchestras and bands.
          Music has the ability to evoke a wide range of emotions and can be
          used in a variety of settings, from concerts and festivals to films
          and television shows.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="section">
        <h2>Technology</h2>
        <p>
          Technology is the use of scientific knowledge and resources to create
          tools, machines, and systems that solve problems and improve our
          lives. It encompasses a wide range of fields, including computer
          science, engineering, and healthcare. Technology is constantly
          evolving and is an important aspect of modern society.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="section">
        <h2>Physical Education</h2>
        <p>
          Physical education is the study of physical activity and its impact on
          human health and well-being. It involves the teaching of proper
          exercise technique, healthy habits, and sport skills. Physical
          education promotes the development of physical fitness, coordination,
          and self-esteem, and it is an important aspect of a well-rounded
          education.
        </p>
      </div>
